body: Although easily corrected by the user, I think it's still a high-priority bug because it doesn't correctly match what programs that read the V2 format expect to find. I'm surprised that nobody noticed this all through the multiple alphas and betas, but here we are!

issue.title: Add support for NUnit 3 xml format

repository.name: reportunit
repository.description: ReportUnit - report generator for the test-runner family

issue.body:
NUnit 3 was released a couple of weeks ago. It's output format is fairly different than the NUnit 2 format, so it should probably have a separate parser.

As a temporary workaround, NUnit 3 can output XML in v2 format with the `--result=nunit2.xml;format=nunit2` command line.

One way to identify the two formats is that the root element for v2 is `test-results` whereas it is `test-run` for v3.

For reference, here are results for the same tests in v2 and v3 format. Note, there is a bug in the v2 format produced by NUnit 3 (nunit/nunit#1042) where the categories are reported as properties. This will hopefully be fixed in a release next week.

issue.title: Categories, properties and test-case names are now correctly written for NUnit 2 format

body:
There is also a difference when you run nunit3 with output to nunit2 format. test-suite type was ParameterizedTest in Nunit2 and now it is ParameterizedMethod
Nunit2
`
<test-suite type="ParameterizedTest" name="PointTest" executed="True" result="Success" success="True" time="0.068" asserts="0">
    <results>
        <test-case name="PointTest("String","a")" executed="True" result="Success" success="True" time="0.016" asserts="2" />
        <test-case name="PointTest("String[]",System.String[])" executed="True" result="Success" success="True" time="0.005" asserts="2" />
    </results>
</test-suite>
`
Nunit3
`
<test-suite type="ParameterizedMethod" name="PointTest" executed="True" result="Success" success="True" time="0.026" asserts="48">
    <results>
        <test-case name="PointTest("String","a")" executed="True" result="Success" success="True" time="0.016" asserts="2" />
        <test-case name="PointTest("String[]",System.String[])" executed="True" result="Success" success="True" time="0.005" asserts="2" />
    </results>
</test-suite>
`
@imakowski thanks for the report. Rather than track this in a closed issue, I am going to create a new issue for it.

Since this reported issue has been fixed , closed and released in an update, it would be better to report a new issue if the problem affects your reports. It will get attention that way. Of course, any transforms that just look at test cases won't be affected.

issue.title: NUnit 2 test results report ParameterizedMethod but should be ParameterizedTest

milestone.description:
In the 3.4 release, we plan to improve the engine to allow it to run tests targeting platforms and .NET frameworks that are currently only supported through NUnitLite based runners. This includes platforms like .NET Core and Universal Windows. Ideally, this will also improve the way we run tests on mobile platforms like Android and iOS.

Since these features will be a part of the engine, any runners using the engine will automatically support the new platforms.

In addition, we will be fixing issues and completing enhancements in the backlog in priority order.

We are planning on maintaining a quarterly release cycle and plan on releasing 3.4 at the end of June.

issue.body:
As reported by @imakowski;

There is also a difference when you run nunit3 with output to nunit2 format. test-suite type was ParameterizedTest in Nunit2 and now it is ParameterizedMethod
### Nunit2

``` xml
<test-suite type="ParameterizedTest" name="PointTest" executed="True" result="Success" success="True" time="0.068" asserts="0">
    <results>
        <test-case name="PointTest("String","a")" executed="True" result="Success" success="True" time="0.016" asserts="2" />
        <test-case name="PointTest("String[]",System.String[])" executed="True" result="Success" success="True" time="0.005" asserts="2" />
    </results>
</test-suite>
```
### Nunit3

``` xml
<test-suite type="ParameterizedMethod" name="PointTest" executed="True" result="Success" success="True" time="0.026" asserts="48">
    <results>
        <test-case name="PointTest("String","a")" executed="True" result="Success" success="True" time="0.016" asserts="2" />
        <test-case name="PointTest("String[]",System.String[])" executed="True" result="Success" success="True" time="0.005" asserts="2" />
    </results>
</test-suite>
```
